{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480168"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:38:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:38:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.53,0.07,0.07,0.2]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"20"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41803"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"20","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/20"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26751"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"1196"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"943"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3749"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36914"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41956"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42951"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41803","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/41803"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 89-year-old man presents to his General Practice clinic for a routine health check-up. He presented to his General Practitioner six months ago with a blood pressure of 170/100mmHg and was prescribed ramipril (2.5mg oral once daily). Three months later his blood pressure had not improved and amlodipine (2.5mg oral once daily) was added. He has a medical history of stable angina. His medications, other than those previously mentioned, include glyceryl trinitrate sublingual spray PRN. He is compliant with his medications. He is a non-smoker and drinks two to four glasses of wine per week. He walks for 40 minutes four times a week, has a balanced diet and is not obese. Today his blood pressure is 160/90 mmHg.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following management plans is most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Change the amlodipine to a thiazide diuretic","Increase the dose of ramipril","Change the ramipril to a beta-blocker","Continue both medications at their current dosages","Increase the dose of both medications"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMost anti-hypertensives can be expected to reach maximum effect within 4-6 weeks. Accordingly, the current Heart Foundation guidelines recommend that when blood pressure targets are not met within 3 months of starting a second agent, \u003Cstrong\u003Eincrease the dose of one of the medications\u003C/strong\u003E. If the lower dose has been well-tolerated, the side effect profile of a dose increase is likely to be more predictable than either changing agents or adding a third. Indeed, older people are at an increased risk of adverse effects such as hypotension, falls, and syncope; medication adjustments should be made carefully.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe combination this patient is on - an ACE inhibitor and a calcium channel blocker - is appropriate for the patient\u0027s age and comorbidities, so there is \u003Cstrong\u003Eno particular impetus to switch agents\u003C/strong\u003E, either to a \u003Cstrong\u003Ebeta-blocker\u003C/strong\u003E or a \u003Cstrong\u003Ethiazide diuretic\u003C/strong\u003E. These agents might have been a good choice of initial treatment if the patient had a history of myocardial infarction, heart failure, and/or stroke.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe treatment of hypertension in older persons is important because hypertension is a risk factor for cardiovascular mortality and morbidity. The landmark HYVET trial (Hypertension in the Very Elderly) demonstrated significant reductions in all-cause mortality (21%), cardiovascular events (34%), and stroke (30%) in the over-80 age group.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["If blood pressure targets are not reached \u003E3 months after starting a second agent at low dose, increase the dose of one of the agents rather than switching or adding a third"],"references":["National Heart Foundation of Australia: Guideline for the diagnosis and management of hypertension in adults [online]. 2016. Available at: https://www.heartfoundation.org.au/getmedia/c83511ab-835a-4fcf-96f5-88d770582ddc/PRO-167_Hypertension-guideline-2016_WEB.pdf","Beckett et al; HYVET Study Group. Treatment of hypertension in patients 80 years of age or older. N Engl J Med. 2008;358(18):1887-98. Available at: https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/nejmoa0801369"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26751"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/26751"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-01-23T20:48:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-01-23T20:48:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"20"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41803"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position"